[[File:Chalk Art.JPG|thumb|Positive behavior is seen in students when they can draw on the chalkboard]]
'''Chalkboard art''' or '''chalk art''' is the use of [[chalk]] on a [[blackboard]] as a [[visual art]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Whitney|first1=Frederick|title=Blackboard sketching|date=1909|publisher=Milton Bradley company|url=https://archive.org/details/blackboardsketch00whit|language=en}}</ref> It is similar to art using [[pastel]]s and related to [[sidewalk art]] that often uses chalk. Chalkboard art is often used in restaurants, shops or walls.<ref name=stub>{{cite book|last1=Stum|first1=Tracy Lee|title=The Art of Chalk: Techniques and Inspiration for Creating Art with Chalk|date=2016|publisher=Rockport Publishers|isbn=9781631590665|page=9|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=WIazCwAAQBAJ|language=en}}</ref>

