'''Jakob Ulrich''' (23 September 1856, in [[Waltalingen]] &ndash; 5 September 1906, in [[Zürich]]) was a Swiss [[Romance languages|Romance philologist]].
He studied [[Indo-European languages|Indo-European linguistics]] and Romance philology in [[University of Zürich|Zürich]] and Paris, where his teachers included [[Gaston Paris]] and [[Paul Meyer (philologist)|Paul Meyer]]. In 1879 he received his doctorate at Zürich under the direction of [[Heinrich Schweizer-Sidler]] with the thesis ''Die formelle Entwicklung des Participium Praeteriti in den romanischen Sprachen''. In 1880 he obtained his [[habilitation]] for Romance philology at the University of Zürich, where in 1901 he attained a full professorship. After his death, he was succeeded at the university by [[Louis Gauchat]].<ref>[http://www.hls-dhs-dss.ch/textes/d/D46378.php Ulrich, Jakob] Historischen Lexikon der Schweiz</ref><ref>[http://lexikon.romanischestudien.de/index.php?title=Ulrich,_Jakob_(Jacob,_Giacomo) Ulrich, Jakob (Jacob, Giacomo)] Romanistenlexikon</ref>
== Selected works == * ''Rhätoromanische Chrestomathie'', 1882 &ndash; [[Raeto-Romance]] [[chrestomathy]]. * ''Rhätoromanische texte'', 1883 &ndash; Raeto-Romance text. * ''Altitalienisches lesebuch, XIII. jahrhundert, zusammengestellt'', 1886 &ndash; Old Italian primer of the 13th century. * ''Robert von Blois Sämmtliche Werke''; as editor (3 volumes, 1889–95) &ndash; [[Robert de Blois]]' collected works. * ''Französische Volkslieder'', 1899 &ndash; French folk songs. * ''Trubert. Altfranzösischer schelmenroman des Douin de Lavesne''; as editor, 1904 &ndash; Trubert; Old French picaresque novel of Douin de Lavesne. * ''Die hundert alten Erzählungen'', 1905 &ndash; 100 old narratives. * ''Romanische schelmennovellen'', 1905 &ndash; [[Romansh language|Romansh]] picaresque novels. * ''Proben der lateinischen Novellistik des Mittelalters'', 1906 &ndash; Samples of Latin novelistic during the Middle Ages. * ''Der engadinische Psalter des Chiampel'' (as editor, 1906) &ndash; The [[Engadin]] [[psalter]] of Ulrich Campell.<ref>[http://worldcat.org/identities/lccn-nr98018019/ Most widely held works about Jakob Ulrich] WorldCat Identities</ref>
